    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "Eve had been perfectly happy by her husband&apos;s side in her Eden home; but, like restless modern Eves, she was flattered with the hope of entering a higher sphere than that which God had assigned her. In attempting to rise above her original position, she fell far below it. A similar result will be reached by all who are unwilling to take up cheerfully their life duties in accordance with God&apos;s plan.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">4<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"PP 58.1\" data-link=\"84.188\">Patriarchs and Prophets, 58, 59</span>.</span></a></sup>",
