    "refcode_long": "The Adventist Home, p. 115.3 (Ellen Gould White)",
    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "<strong>Wives Submit; Husbands Love</strong>&mdash;The question is often asked, &ldquo;Shall a wife have no will of her own?&rdquo; The Bible plainly states that the husband is the head of the family. &ldquo;Wives, submit yourselves unto your own husbands.&rdquo; If this injunction ended here, we might say <span class=\"page-break\" data-page=\"116\"></span> that the position of the wife is not an enviable one; it is a very hard and trying position in very many cases, and it would be better were there fewer marriages. Many husbands stop at the words, &ldquo;Wives, submit yourselves,&rdquo; but we will read the conclusion of the same injunction, which is, &ldquo;As it is fit in the Lord.&rdquo;",
    "puborder": 323,
