    "refcode_long": "The Adventist Home, p. 117.3 (Ellen Gould White)",
    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "Let every husband and father study to understand the words of Christ, not in a one-sided manner, merely dwelling upon the subjection of the wife to her husband, but in the light of the cross of Calvary, study as to his own position in the family circle. &ldquo;Husbands, love your wives, even as Christ also loved the church, and gave Himself for it; that He might sanctify and cleanse it with the washing of water by the word.&rdquo; Jesus gave Himself up to die upon the cross in order that He might cleanse <span class=\"page-break\" data-page=\"118\"></span> and keep us from all sin and pollution by the influence of the Holy Spirit.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">6<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"Ms 17, 1891\" data-link=\"14057.6457001\">Manuscript 17, 1891</span>.</span></a></sup>",
