    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "Unless men and women have learned of Christ, His meekness and lowliness, they will reveal the impulsive, unreasonable spirit so often revealed by children. The strong, undisciplined will will seek to rule. Such ones <span class=\"page-break\" data-page=\"119\"></span> need to study the words of Paul: &ldquo;When I was a child, I spake as a child, I understood as a child, I thought as a child: but when I became a man, I put away childish things.&rdquo;<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">10<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"Lt 55, 1902\" data-link=\"14067.10667001\">Letter 55, 1902</span>.</span></a></sup>",
