    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "<strong>Adjusting Family Difficulties</strong>&mdash;It is a hard matter to adjust family difficulties, even when husband and wife seek to make a fair and just settlement in regard to their several duties, if they have failed to submit the heart to God. How can husband and wife divide the interests of their home life and still keep a loving, firm hold upon each other? They should have a united interest in all that concerns their homemaking, and the wife, if a Christian, will have her interest with her husband as his companion; for the husband is to stand as the head of the household.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">11<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"Ms 31, 1911\" data-link=\"14075.10939001\">Manuscript 31, 1911</span>.</span></a></sup>",
