    "refcode_long": "The Adventist Home, p. 119.3 (Ellen Gould White)",
    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "My brother, my sister, open the door of the heart to receive Jesus. Invite him into the soul-temple. Help each other to overcome the obstacles which enter the married life of all. You will have a fierce conflict to overcome <span class=\"page-break\" data-page=\"120\"></span> your adversary the devil, and if you expect God to help you in this battle, you must both unite in deciding to overcome, to seal your lips against speaking any words of wrong, even if you have to fall upon your knees and cry aloud, &ldquo;Lord, rebuke the adversary of my soul.&rdquo;<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">13<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"Lt 105, 1893\" data-link=\"14058.5121001\">Letter 105, 1893</span>.</span></a></sup>",
